      </div>
      <a href="https://mytoywagon.com/products/q-toys-wooden-weaving-station" class="view-pdp" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:16px;">Weaving Frame &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; MTW-CA-QWS &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; View product &rarr;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="col-txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">Essay One &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; The Slow Work</span>
      <h3>Patience, attention, and a little mess <span class="it">lead somewhere worth going.</span></h3>

      <div class="body">
        <p><span class="dropcap">M</span>aking is the lesson. A child threads twine and leaves through a weaving frame and learns rhythm before she has the word for it. She presses a flower between sheets of paper and meets the slow patience of preserving. She stamps shapes from eco-cutters and discovers that a story can be told by a shape pressed into clay. Creative Arts is the toolkit for that making. No instructions. No worksheets. Just material, tool, and the long quiet hour where a child practices being a maker.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);">
        <div class="p"><span class="label">To Weave</span><p>Twine and leaves through wood. Rhythm before language.</p></div>
        <div class="p"><span class="label">To Press</span><p>Flowers, leaves, the slow patience of the heirloom press.</p></div>
        <div class="p"><span class="label">To Stamp</span><p>Eco-cutters into clay. The shape of an idea, pressed.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


